Brazil Prosecutor Challenges Soccer World Cup Budget Rules, Folha Reports

-- B y   K a r e n   E e u w e n s
-- 
2011-09-07T09:22:07Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-07/brazil-prosecutor-challenges-soccer-world-cup-budget-rules-folha-reports.html
Brazil ’s Chief Federal Prosecutor
Roberto Gurgel plans a Supreme Court challenge to new rules
allowing preliminary budgets for projects linked to the 2014
soccer  World Cup  and 2016  Olympic Games  to be kept secret during
the auction phase, Folha de S. Paulo reported.  Gurgel’s aim is to prevent the rules from leading to
unnecessary public spending, Folha cited him as saying.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Karen Eeuwens in London at 
 keeuwens@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
